title_sort: louisa van velsor whitman to walt whitman, [7 october 1871]
title: Louisa Van Velsor Whitman to Walt Whitman, [7 October 1871]
text: 30 Sept 1871SaturdaySaturday morning My dear waltWalti thought i must send you a line to tell you i have got all the letters and the order came very good and the book by georg sandGeorge Sand and all the papers and best of all the green porters has left early this morning for home georgeGeorge and loo came last night fridayFriday night quite late and have gone over to the institute to day Jeff has gone to bostonBoston look for him home to knightnight or to morrow he went fishing wensdayWednesday and caught lots of very large blue fish he brought home 2 it was first rate one of the men from st louisSt. Louis was here with Jeff matt must be home by this time O waltWalt i am so thankful to you for your kindness to me in sending me money at all times good bie walterWalter dear)i have had a letter from mrsMrs. hind she thank you for your donation and has got the poem and wants you to send one to townsendTownsend) tomTom romeRome is married to a scotch girl Louisa Van Velsor Whitman to Walt Whitman, [7 October 1871]
